---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About">
  <section and-layout="vertical gap:xl" class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-24">

    <div and-layout="vertical gap:sm">
      <and-badge variant="outline" class="w-fit">About</and-badge>
      <h1 and-text="h2 weight:bold">What is astro-dx?</h1>
    </div>

    <and-alert variant="info">
      <strong>Community library</strong> — astro-dx is not affiliated with,
      endorsed by, or part of the official Astro project.
    </and-alert>

    <div and-layout="vertical gap:md">
      <p and-text="p" class="opacity-80">
        Astro is great for content-focused sites with zero JS by default.
        But when you need client-side interactivity across islands,
        the DX gets rough — raw nanostores, manual querySelector, no cleanup.
      </p>
      <p and-text="p" class="opacity-80">
        astro-dx brings Angular patterns — signals, computed values,
        singleton services, declarative DOM bindings — to Astro client scripts.
        No compiler, no framework overhead.
      </p>
    </div>

    <and-accordion>
      <and-accordion-item>
        <span slot="header">Why not just use Preact or Vue islands?</span>
        <p slot="content" and-text="p-sm" class="opacity-70">
          You can — and sometimes you should. astro-dx fills the gap for
          components that need interactivity but not a full framework.
        </p>
      </and-accordion-item>
      <and-accordion-item>
        <span slot="header">Why not Alpine.js?</span>
        <p slot="content" and-text="p-sm" class="opacity-70">
          Alpine uses eval() for expressions. astro-dx keeps all logic
          in TypeScript with full type safety.
        </p>
      </and-accordion-item>
      <and-accordion-item>
        <span slot="header">Does it work with Cloudflare Pages?</span>
        <p slot="content" and-text="p-sm" class="opacity-70">
          Yes. astro-dx is fully static. Built specifically with
          Cloudflare + Astro in mind.
        </p>
      </and-accordion-item>
    </and-accordion>

  </section>
</BaseLayout>
